      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 11
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and rotary performance. This example features the original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged engine, delivering linear power through its factory-spec vacuum-controlled boost system. The chassis integrity is unparalleled, featuring the original four-wheel double-wishbone aluminum suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential that ensures optimal torque distribution. Every component, from the graphite-reinforced apex seals to the high-efficiency cooling system, has been maintained to exacting standards. The exterior retains its factory-applied finish with perfect panel alignment, while the cockpit remains a time capsule of driver-centric ergonomics. This is a rare opportunity to own a mechanically synchronized FD that has never seen aftermarket modification, preserving its legendary 50/50 weight distribution and tactile steering feedback.",
